# CODEOWNERS — controls automatic review assignment for pull requests.
#
# Syntax: <path pattern> <owner1> [<owner2> ...]
# Patterns matched later in the file override earlier ones.
# Reference: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositories-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Today this repository is maintained by a single owner. As contributors join
# the project, add their handles next to the paths they own — start with the
# less-sensitive paths (a single source adapter, a single pattern doc) and
# only widen ownership over time. Governance files (LICENSE, NOTICE,
# TRADEMARKS, NORMS, SECURITY, .github/) stay narrowly owned.

# ── Default owner for all paths ──────────────────────────────────────────
* @joshuarweaver

# ── Repository governance ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# These files set the legal, security, and community-conduct baseline for
# the project. Changes here propagate to every contributor and should be
# reviewed with extra care.
/LICENSE                @joshuarweaver
/NOTICE                 @joshuarweaver
/NOTICE.md              @joshuarweaver
/TRADEMARKS.md          @joshuarweaver
/NORMS.md               @joshuarweaver
/SECURITY.md            @joshuarweaver
/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md     @joshuarweaver
/CONTRIBUTING.md        @joshuarweaver
/README.md              @joshuarweaver
/.github/               @joshuarweaver

